description:
The Position

The Position

A healthier future. It‚Äôs what drives us to innovate. To continuously advance science and ensure everyone has access to the healthcare they need today and for generations to come. Creating a world where we all have more time with the people we love. That‚Äôs what makes us Genentech. ‚Äã

The Opportunity

At Genentech Computational Sciences (gCS) Prescient Design, we are revolutionizing drug discovery with cutting-edge machine learning techniques. We are seeking talented engineers with a passion for building large-scale, distributed machine learning algorithms and systems that will transform the drug discovery process.

gCS Prescient Design is seeking an exceptional Machine Learning Engineer to develop our core Foundation Models and enable the next generation of machine learning for drug discovery. We are looking for someone who is not only passionate about technical problem-solving but also has a proven track record of delivering innovative solutions in AI/ML. The ideal candidate should have extensive experience in leading and managing a team of engineers and scientists, and be able to foster a culture of innovation, collaboration, and excellence across the broader gCS organization.

The group provides a dynamic and challenging environment for multidisciplinary research including access to heterogeneous data sources, close links to top academic institutions around the world, as well as collaborations with internal Genentech and Roche teams.

In this role, you will:

‚óè Participate in cutting-edge research and development in LLMs for various, cutting-edge internal applications including drug discovery/development and biomedical problems. ‚óè Develop LLMs including data engineering, pretraining, finetuning, post-training, and evaluation as well as deploy models in production environments, working closely with other engineers to ensure scalability and reliability

‚óè Solve core ML and engineering challenges including the design, implementation, and scaling of our data, training, and deployment pipeline

‚óè Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams across both Prescient Design and gRED to solve complex problems in the life sciences

Who You Are:

‚óè You have an MS/BS in Computer Science, Statistics, related field, or equivalent experience and 2+ years of industry experience in machine learning; or a PhD in Computer Science and related field and 0+ years of industry experience.

‚óè You have demonstrated success in technical capabilities deploying machine learning models in production environments or in ML/LLM research

‚óè You have strong programming skills in Python

‚óè You have extensive experience with deep learning/LLMs.

‚óè A dynamic and resilient individual who excels in a rapidly evolving environment, taking initiative on projects and continuously learning and adapting to new challenges and opportunities.

‚óè A collaborative and open-minded team player who values constructive feedback, refrains from judgment, and fosters a positive and respectful team environment.

‚óè Strong communication skills, with the ability to effectively communicate technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences as well as interfacing with scientific and engineering leadership

‚óè A passion for solving complex technical problems and a commitment to staying up-to-date with the latest developments in machine learning

‚óè Experience collaborating with external scientific partners, such as academic institutions or industry research groups

‚óè An extensive track record of delivering innovative solutions in machine learning

Relocation benefits are available for this job posting

The expected salary range for this position based on the primary location of New York City is $141,100 - $262,100 of hiring range. Actual pay will be determined based on experience, qualifications, geographic location, and other job-related factors permitted by law. A discretionary annual bonus may be available based on individual and Company performance. This position also qualifies for the benefits detailed at the link provided below.

Benefits

Genentech is an equal opportunity employer. It is our policy and practice to employ, promote, and otherwise treat any and all employees and applicants on the basis of merit, qualifications, and competence. The company's policy prohibits unlawful discrimination, including but not limited to, discrimination on the basis of Protected Veteran status, individuals with disabilities status, and consistent with all federal, state, or local laws.

If you have a disability and need an accommodation in relation to the online application process, please contact us by completing this form Accommodations for Applicants.

description:
The goal of a Machine Learning Engineer at Scale is to bring techniques in the fields of computer vision, deep learning and deep reinforcement learning, or natural language processing into a production environment to improve Scale's products and customer experience. Our research engineers take advantage of our unique access to massive datasets to deliver improvements to our customers.

We are building a large hybrid human-machine system in service of ML pipelines for Federal Government customers. We currently complete millions of tasks a month, and will grow to complete billions of tasks monthly.
You will:
‚Ä¢ Take state of the art models developed internally and from the community, use them in production to solve problems for our customers and taskers.
‚Ä¢ Take models currently in production, identify areas for improvement, improve them using retraining and hyperparameter searches, then deploy without regressing on core model characteristics
‚Ä¢ Work with product and research teams to identify opportunities for improvement in our current product line and for enabling upcoming product lines
‚Ä¢ Work with massive datasets to develop both generic models as well as fine tune models for specific products
‚Ä¢ Build the scalable ML platform to automate our ML service
‚Ä¢ Be a representative for how to apply machine learning and related techniques throughout the engineering and product organization
‚Ä¢ Be able, and willing, to multi-task and learn new technologies quickly
‚Ä¢ This role will require an active security clearance or the ability to obtain a security clearance.
Ideally You‚Äôd Have:
‚Ä¢ Extensive experience using computer vision, deep learning and deep reinforcement Learning, or natural language processing in a production environment
‚Ä¢ Solid background in algorithms, data structures, and object-oriented programming
‚Ä¢ Strong programing skills in Python or Javascript, experience in Tensorflow or PyTorch

Nice to Haves:
‚Ä¢ Graduate degree in Computer Science, Machine Learning or Artificial Intelligence specialization
‚Ä¢ Experience working with cloud technology stack (eg. AWS or GCP) and developing machine learning models in a cloud environment
‚Ä¢ Experience with generative AI models

Compensation packages at Scale for eligible roles include base salary, equity, and benefits. The range displayed on each job posting reflects the minimum and maximum target for new hire salaries for the position, determined by work location and additional factors, including job-related skills, experience, interview performance, and relevant education or training. Scale employees in eligible roles are also granted equity based compensation, subject to Board of Director approval. Your recruiter can share more about the specific salary range for your preferred location during the hiring process, and confirm whether the hired role will be eligible for equity grant. You‚Äôll also receive benefits including, but not limited to: Comprehensive health, dental and vision coverage, retirement benefits, a learning and development stipend, and generous PTO. Additionally, this role may be eligible for additional benefits such as a commuter stipend.

Please reference the job posting's subtitle for where this position will be located. For pay transparency purposes, the base salary range for this full-time position in the locations of San Francisco, New York, Seattle is:

$224,400‚Äî$293,250 USD

Please reference the job posting's subtitle for where this position will be located. For pay transparency purposes, the base salary range for this full-time position in the locations of Washington DC, Texas, Colorado is:

$201,960‚Äî$263,925 USD

PLEASE NOTE: Our policy requires a 90-day waiting period before reconsidering candidates for the same role. This allows us to ensure a fair and thorough evaluation of all applicants.

About Us:

At Scale, we believe that the transition from traditional software to AI is one of the most important shifts of our time. Our mission is to make that happen faster across every industry, and our team is transforming how organizations build and deploy AI. Our products power the world's most advanced LLMs, generative models, and computer vision models. We are trusted by generative AI companies such as OpenAI, Meta, and Microsoft, government agencies like the U.S. Army and U.S. Air Force, and enterprises including GM and Accenture. We are expanding our team to accelerate the development of AI applications.

We believe that everyone should be able to bring their whole selves to work, which is why we are proud to be an inclusive and equal opportunity workplace. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability status, gender identity or Veteran status.

We are committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with physical and mental disabilities. If you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation in the application or recruiting process due to a disability, please contact us at accommodations@scale.com. Please see the United States Department of Labor's Know Your Rights poster for additional information.

We comply with the United States Department of Labor's Pay Transparency provision.

PLEASE NOTE: We collect, retain and use personal data for our professional business purposes, including notifying you of job opportunities that may be of interest and sharing with our affiliates. We limit the personal data we collect to that which we believe is appropriate and necessary to manage applicants‚Äô needs, provide our services, and comply with applicable laws. Any information we collect in connection with your application will be treated in accordance with our internal policies and programs designed to protect personal data. Please see our privacy policy for additional information.

job_title: Principal Agentic AI Machine Learning Engineer
description:
Who we are‚Ä¶

In a world of constant change, we're leading the charge towards truly autonomous enterprises. Our cutting-edge platform harnesses the power of automation and generative AI to revolutionize how businesses manage and optimize their IT operations.

We're not just adapting to digital transformation‚Äîwe're accelerating it. Our solutions bring business and operations leaders together, unlocking new levels of innovation, efficiency, and scalability. We empower organizations to deliver superior customer experiences and drive revenue growth in an always-on, always-mobile world.

We are leading the charge toward truly autonomous enterprises with our Skylar AI platform‚Äîan advanced AI suite that revolutionizes IT operations by harnessing generative AI, unsupervised machine learning, and human-in-the-loop automation. Skylar AI delivers deep autonomous real-time data visualization, exploration, and advanced analytics to help organizations stay ahead in an increasingly complex and competitive digital landscape.

What we're looking for‚Ä¶

ScienceLogic is seeking an experienced Agentic AI Machine Learning Engineer specializing in LLMs and autonomous agents and agentic AI to work on an innovative AI-driven orchestration engine that empowers organizations to automate complex workflows through intelligent, proprietary and 3rd Party AI agents.

We are looking for people with a very technical background in software development across multiple technology stacks in the development of highly scalable software services and systems.

What you'll be doing...
‚Ä¢ Architect and lead the development of scalable, robust AI orchestration frameworks that enable autonomous, agentic AI systems to collaborate and execute complex tasks.
‚Ä¢ Design and build LLM powered proprietary AI agents and services capable of reasoning, learning, and adapting within dynamic IT environments.
‚Ä¢ Drive innovation in multi-agent orchestration, including task decomposition, dynamic scheduling, and adaptive control strategies.
‚Ä¢ Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams‚Äîproduct management, data science, software engineering‚Äîto translate business needs into technical solutions.
‚Ä¢ Ensure the reliability, security, and performance of agentic AI systems in production.
‚Ä¢ Mentor and guide engineering teams on best practices in AI system design and agent-based architectures.
‚Ä¢ Stay at the forefront of AI research, applying advances in reinforcement learning, automated reasoning, and distributed AI to enhance Skylar capabilities.
‚Ä¢ Contribute to ScienceLogic's intellectual property and represent the company in technical forums

Qualities you possess‚Ä¶
‚Ä¢ 10+ years of experience in software engineering focused on AI, autonomous systems, or multi-agent architectures.
‚Ä¢ Master's or PhD in Computer Science, AI, Robotics, or related field preferred; bachelor's degree is required.
‚Ä¢ Research experience in LLM and agentic orchestration.
‚Ä¢ Proven expertise in designing and implementing agent-based systems and orchestration frameworks.
‚Ä¢ Strong programming skills in Python, C++, or Java.
‚Ä¢ Experience with AI/ML frameworks such as LangChain, LangGraph,TensorFlow or PyTorch, and reinforcement learning techniques.
‚Ä¢ Deep understanding of distributed systems, concurrency, and scalable software design.
‚Ä¢ Familiarity with natural language processing, knowledge representation, and automated reasoning is a plus.
‚Ä¢ Excellent leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills.
‚Ä¢ Track record of delivering complex AI projects from concept to production.
‚Ä¢ Domain experience in Network Monitoring, Infrastructure Monitoring, Machine Learning/AI, scalable architectures, Cloud (Private, Public, Hybrid) Technologies, Design and operational expertise in Software as a Service (Saas) systems is a big plus.

Benefits & Perks
‚Ä¢ Flexible work arrangements supporting work-life balance.
‚Ä¢ Comprehensive medical, dental and vision plans.
‚Ä¢ 401(k) plan with employer match.
‚Ä¢ Flexible Paid Time Off (FTO) so that you can take the time that you need to re-energize.
‚Ä¢ Volunteer Time Off (VTO) - take two days off per calendar year to volunteer with your preferred charitable organization.
‚Ä¢ 5-year Service Milestone Sabbatical.
‚Ä¢ Paid parental leave.
‚Ä¢ Generous employee referral bonus program.
‚Ä¢ Pet insurance.
‚Ä¢ HQ Office centrally located in Reston Town Center featuring a well-stocked kitchen with rotating snacks and beverages, and catered lunch on Thursdays.
‚Ä¢ Regular virtual company-wide events, including cooking classes, yoga, meditation and more.
‚Ä¢ The opportunity to learn and develop from some of the best and brightest minds in the industry!

Don't meet every single requirement? Studies have shown that women and people of color are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single qualification. At ScienceLogic, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive and authentic workplace, so if you're excited about this role but your past experience doesn't align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.

All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, or any other applicable legally protected characteristics in the location in which you are applying.

About ScienceLogic

ScienceLogic empowers intelligent, automated IT operations, freeing up time and resources, and driving business outcomes with actionable insights. ScienceLogic's AIOps platform sees broadly across clouds and on-premises, enabling business service visibility with relationship mapping, and workflow automation to eliminate manual tasks. Trusted by thousands of organizations across the globe, ScienceLogic's technology has been proven for scale by the world's largest service providers, enterprises and government agencies.

About Skylar AI

Skylar AI is ScienceLogic's groundbreaking suite of advanced AI capabilities designed to revolutionize IT operations (ITOps). Leveraging GenAI and agentic AI, Skylar AI reasons over telemetry and stored knowledge to deliver accurate predictions, context-rich recommendations, and intelligent automations. Its core services‚ÄîSkylar Advisor, Skylar Analytics, and Skylar Automated Root Cause Analysis‚Äîenable proactive management, rapid troubleshooting, and exceptional customer experiences by automating complex operational tasks and anticipating issues before they occur.

www.sciencelogic.com

All ScienceLogic employees have the responsibility to protect information assets, adhere to access controls, report suspicious activity, and comply with security and privacy policies.

description:
Position: Data Scientist
Our client, a fast-growing and innovative technology company in the hospitality sector, is seeking a talented and motivated Data Scientist to join their expanding Data Science team.
If you have a strong foundation in machine learning and programming‚Äîwhether your background is in Computer Science, Mathematics, Engineering, Physics, or any other quantitative discipline‚Äîthis is an exciting opportunity to make an immediate impact.

About the Company
This company provides cutting-edge B2B SaaS solutions designed to help hotel brands increase direct bookings by optimizing the guest booking experience and reclaiming their share of online revenue. With a diverse, international team based in Barcelona and other key locations worldwide, the company combines deep expertise in hospitality, product design, and consumer marketing to deliver pioneering technology that benefits thousands of hotels globally.

The Role
The Data Science team plays a central role in shaping the future of the platform by applying advanced machine learning techniques across multiple domains, including user behavior prediction, natural language processing (NLP), large language models (LLMs), computer vision, time-series forecasting, and causal inference.
Working with a unique dataset derived from millions of daily user sessions on thousands of hotel websites, the team develops AI-powered products that lead the market in personalization and performance.

Predictive Systems: Machine learning models forecasting user behaviors such as purchase likelihood, price sensitivity, and travel flexibility, enabling personalized experiences through targeted messaging.
AI-Driven Web Content Analysis: NLP-based tools analyzing content across numerous hotel websites, combined with extensive behavioral data to provide actionable insights that improve the customer journey.
AI-Powered Personalization: Recommendation engines using LLMs to automatically tailor web tools for each property, maximizing the effectiveness of direct booking strategies.

Why Join This Team?
The Data Science team is at the core of the company‚Äôs innovation, developing and deploying advanced ML and AI techniques that power high-impact products used daily by clients worldwide. Joining the team means contributing to a fast-paced environment where your work will directly influence key product features affecting millions of travelers.

What We‚Äôre Looking For
Bachelor‚Äôs degree in a quantitative discipline such as Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, Engineering, or similar.
3+ years of industry experience applying machine learning techniques.
Proven experience managing data science projects end-to-end, from ideation to implementation and delivery.
Strong theoretical and practical knowledge of machine learning and statistics.
Proficiency in Python and familiarity with key ML libraries (e.g., pandas, numpy, scikit-learn, TensorFlow/Keras or PyTorch, matplotlib, seaborn, FastAPI).
Strong problem-solving skills with a proactive and resourceful approach.
Self-motivated, creative, and eager to learn new technologies and methodologies.

Nice to Have
Experience with workflow orchestration tools like Airflow and messaging systems such as Apache Kafka.
Familiarity with cloud platforms, especially AWS (e.g., S3, ECR).
Experience with containerization and orchestration technologies like Docker and Kubernetes.
Comfortable with Linux environments, version control (Git/GitHub), and CI/CD pipelines.
Experience handling large datasets.
Hands-on experience with Deep Learning frameworks, particularly PyTorch.
Knowledge of deploying retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) and agentic workflows.
Understanding of best practices in production environments including testing, documentation, and maintenance.
Master‚Äôs degree in a relevant field is a plus.

What the Company Offers
Competitive salary package.
A truly international team with 25+ nationalities.
Work from a central office in Barcelona.
Opportunity to have a real impact on a fast-growing tech company.
Ongoing training and development opportunities.
Healthy work-life balance with flexible hours and a hybrid remote policy (3 days remote per week).
Flexible benefits including meal, transport, and nursery vouchers.
Perks like coffee, tea, fresh fruit, and weekly team breakfasts.
Exclusive discounts at hotels worldwide.

description: Data Analyst - Analista de Datos - El SalvadorDI is seeking to hire a Data Analyst to support UNDP's Prudencia: Citizen Voices project for a two-month UN-funded research project Listening and Analyzing Digital Narratives about Underrepresented Groups in Public Policy in El Salvador. This project aims to analyze digital conversations around the participation of underrepresented groups, such as women, youth, people with disabilities, Indigenous peoples, and returnees, in public policy processes. The Data Analyst will collect, process, and interpret data from social media platforms, digital forums, and media outlets to identify and map key trends, influencers, sentiment patterns, and disinformation chains. This role will be instrumental in generating data-driven insights that inform final reports and strategic recommendations on strengthening underrepresented groups' participation in public decision-making. The successful candidate will have demonstrated expertise in quantitative and qualitative data analysis, as well as fluent Spanish and English proficiency to navigate relevant digital platforms and sources effectively. This is a short-term consultant position based in Washington, DC or remote and is contingent upon award.
